"title": "5252: chariots",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5252",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Horse-drawn vehicles used for carrying important people when travelling or on ceremonial occasions, and in war for carrying warriors. The chariot is used as a symbol of military power, the power of God and as a picture of God's angelic army.</p>\n<h2>Chariots used for travelling</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen46:29\">GEN 46:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:9\">GEN 50:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg4:15\">JDG 4:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam15:1\">2SA 15:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:18\">1KI 12:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:44\">1KI 18:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs20:33\">1KI 20:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs5:21\">2KI 5:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs9:16\">2KI 9:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs9:21\">2KI 9:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs10:16\">2KI 10:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:28\">ACT 8:28</a></p>\n<h2>Chariots used on ceremonial occasions</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:43\">GEN 41:43</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:9\">GEN 50:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:25\">JER 17:25</a></p>\n<h2>Chariots used for carrying warriors</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:6-Exod14:7\">EXO 14:6–14:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:4\">DEU 11:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut20:1\">DEU 20:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh11:4\">JOS 11:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh17:16\">JOS 17:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg1:19\">JDG 1:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg4:13\">JDG 4:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:11\">1SA 8:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:5\">1SA 13:5</a> <em>the Philistines prepare for battle</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam1:6\">2SA 1:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam8:4\">2SA 8:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr18:4\">1CH 18:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:26\">1KI 10:26</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr1:14\">2CH 1:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs20:1\">1KI 20:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs6:14\">2KI 6:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs8:21\">2KI 8:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs10:2\">2KI 10:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr19:6\">1CH 19:6</a> <em>the Ammonites hire chariots and charioteers</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr12:3\">2CH 12:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr14:9\">2CH 14:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek23:24\">EZK 23:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek26:7\">EZK 26:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek26:10\">EZK 26:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah2:4\">NAM 2:4</a></p>\n<h2>The chariot as a symbol of military might</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps20:7\">PSA 20:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:23\">2KI 19:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:24\">ISA 37:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:7\">ISA 2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa22:7\">ISA 22:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa22:18\">ISA 22:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:1\">ISA 31:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa36:9\">ISA 36:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:37\">JER 50:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:21\">JER 51:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic5:10\">MIC 5:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah2:13\">NAM 2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:22\">HAG 2:22</a></p>\n<h2>The chariot as a symbol of God's mighty power</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:3\">PSA 104:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs2:11\">2KI 2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:4\">PSA 68:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:33\">PSA 68:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:1\">ISA 19:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek1:15-Ezek1:21\">EZK 1:15–1:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech6:1-Zech6:8\">ZEC 6:1–6:8</a></p>\n<h2>God's mighty angelic army depicted by chariots</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs6:17\">2KI 6:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:17\">PSA 68:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:15\">ISA 66:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:13\">JER 4:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab3:8\">HAB 3:8</a></p>",
